Barcelona have agreed a deal with Sevilla to sign versatile wide-man Aleix Vidal for £7.5million, plus performance related add-ons of up to £5m. Vidal is set to put pen to paper on a five-year contract with the Catalan giants after an impressive season in which he played a key part in his team's run to winning the Europa League. The winger, who has frequently been deployed as a right-back this season by coach Unai Emery, is expected to replace Dani Alves - another former Sevilla player - who still hasn't signed a new deal, with his current contract ending on June 30.
